listitem.para:
Target independent &tdf; capsules are linked, using &tld;,
					with the &tdf; libraries to produce target dependent &tdf;
					capsules.

Target dependent &tdf; capsules are translated into
					assembly source files using one of &trans.mips;
					(q.v.—things are not quite so simple in this case), &trans.x86;
					etc.

The &S3.opt; form is similar to the option above, but
						specifies a single input file, &file.arg;
						(which may contain a comma).

The &W2.opt; form is similar to the option above, but
						specifies a single file &str.arg;
						(which may contain a comma).

Is equivalent to inserting the preprocessor directive
						#include "&file.arg;" at the end of each C
						source file.

Is equivalent to inserting the preprocessor directive
						#include "&file.arg;" at the start of each C
						source file.
